arms) endure magic (boots) daring (helm), stun (bracer), cancel magic (gloves) symbol of pinzarn (bp) and spirit str (legs). The bp is nice, and I would upgrade to that, but it's hard to get. The legs would be the most useful, but those are hard to get, too.<br>
Anything else is just lame.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Part of your problem with the paladin class is you are being shortsighted about some of the equipment.  The boots and the arms are pretty useless.  The helm is awesome.  It reduces downtime faster than healing with mana and medding.  Only level 60 priests and level 39+ clerics heal better.  Don't hero yourself.  Use the daring helm instead.  So, you lose about 300 or so HP from not having the top of the line hero spell.  You make a tradeoff for having mana efficiency.  Same goes for the gloves.  What spell do you pull with?  Why not pull with the cancel magic gloves?  They save you mana, and a spell slot.  And as for the bracer...you couldn't be more wrong.  Go scroll up and read what I wrote about how good the bracer is, especially for your weapon selection.<br>
<br>
As for stats, stats don't matter as much as AC.  Keep your stamina over 100, your agility over 75, and don't be encumbered by your own gear, and you are fine.  Paladins are defensive tanks.  Make your AC appropriate to your level with better gear.  Go to icewell and get the boots, gloves, and helm with about 30 minutes work.  Get 1 DW bracer to have options for your role in combat.  Get some guardian armor for resists and AC and some stats.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> The ac would be nice.. but I really need to keep my stats up. Not to mention the vast mana loss I would take.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Paladins don't rely on their mana except for backup heals and stuns and stuff.  If you are worried that you don't have enough mana, then IMO you aren't grouping with the right people.  Healers heal.  Paladins tank with option of backup heal. <p>=============================
<br>Juujuu Bigmojo
<br>60 Halfling Shaman
