<br>
The bracer takes 6 seconds to cast it's 3 second stun. During that 6 seconds, I could have already swung once, or twice if hasted. I could also use the tiny bit of mana (30) to cast the stun spell instead, and it only takes 1.5 seconds to cast. My mana bar doesn't even move when casting it, and if I have c2 on, I gain back the mana before it even recycles. That puts the bracer in the useless catagory.<br>
The helmet CAN heal, but the daring buff takes a LONG time to cast, and only heals 120ish hp. That takes forever if you are trying to fill up even one bub of a warrior. I've used the damn thing, and it's junk. You have to have a daring line of buff or less to be able to use it, and barely anyone wants to take some crappy daring buff over hero or Natureskin. That puts the helmet in the useless catagory.<br>
<br>
Deepwater armor is crap. the ac is great, but the effects are ludicrously stupid. I'm not being shortsighted about this, I've tested ALOT of different tactics, and so far, the way I'm set up now is I have 175wis with a 149str and a 98sta. My big supply of mojo keeps me and the group going for a long time without having to break. I have enough mana to where if the healer(s) need a few minutes to med break, I can take over as primary healer. yes, I've done it before in places like disco and guardian, and never had any problems. When the healers are good on mana, I go towards stunning and nuking. I keep my 3 stuns loaded, as well as my Flame of Light. I time my casts with my swings, and I do well.<br>
<br>
The only area I'm suffering in is AC. I am having a hard time finding decent equipment to replace Valorium that has better ac. To the guy who posted about bracers, yes. Most bracers have the same ac as thier plane bracer. Lambent and Imbued have 10ac. Ro and Valorium have 10ac. etc etc. But the other armor slots are lower than planer armor.<br>
I dont want to kill the dwarves in Icewell because there are good quests there, and it's nice having a city where I can rest at in Velious.<br>
