</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujuujuu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Juujuu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 931<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/28/01 1:36:03 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Paladins... useless?</span><hr size=1> &quot;I'm most of the time medding up to keep my mana high. That puts the gloves in the useless catagory.&quot;<br>
<br>
Some mobs can use a cancel magic every fight.  Necromancers with the dshields come to mind.  If you don't have a slower in group, dispelling the hastes from the shaman is useful.  If you don't have a snarer dispelling the sow from a frog is useful.  If you can't find a use for free dispells, then something is seriously wrong.<br>
<br>
&quot;The bracer takes 6 seconds to cast it's 3 second stun.&quot;<br>
That's a 50% slow.  Togors insects is 60%.  Togor's insects doesn't keep casters from casting.  Togor's insects doesn't stop runners from running away.<br>
<br>
&quot;During that 6 seconds, I could have already swung once, or twice if hasted.&quot;<br>
You aren't an offensive tank.  You are a defensive tank.  Learn your role in the group.<br>
<br>
&quot;I could also use the tiny bit of mana (30) to cast the stun spell instead, and it only takes 1.5 seconds to cast.&quot;<br>
And it has a recast delay of about 10 seconds, making it useless to chain cast.  If you want to chain cast stuns, you need to cycle through your 3 stuns, which ends up costing you 30 mana plus 60 mana, plus about 100 mana.  That's a hell of a lot of mana to do what you can do for free with a bracer.<br>
<br>
Something else that also works is to bracer, then stun with a spell, then bracer, then stun with a spell.  You end up keeping the mob stunned for about 5 seconds at a time, while only marginally reducing your attack rate.  You don't see shaman complaining that they don't get to melee enough while they do the slowing for a group.<br>
<br>
&quot;My mana bar doesn't even move when casting it, and if I have c2 on, I gain back the mana before it even recycles.&quot;<br>
And what do you do when you don't have c2?<br>
<br>
&quot;That puts the bracer in the useless catagory.&quot;<br>
That puts you in the shortsighted category.  The bracer is PROVEN to be useful in combat for slowing and taunting and keeping casters from casting a thing in combat.  If you can't see that, it's no wonder you can't get into groups.<br>
<br>
&quot;The helmet CAN heal, but the daring buff takes a LONG time to cast, and only heals 120ish hp. That takes forever if you are trying to fill up even one bub of a warrior.&quot;<br>
It takes longer to use greater or superior heals and meditate the mana back.  The daring helm with its long cast time is faster healing than any level 59 or lower shaman or druid can do.  It's a fact.  3 darings and you've healed over 300hp.  You can't get back the mana to cast gheal in 30 seconds of sitting and meditating.  It takes longer.  It's a matter of mana efficiency.  The helm is more efficient than using mana to heal.  When I have a paladin in the group with the helm, I INSIST that they don't give me anything but free daring buffs.  It heals faster than anything but a cleric healing.<br>
<br>
&quot;I've used the damn thing, and it's junk.&quot;<br>
Shortsighted.<br>
<br>
&quot;You have to have a daring line of buff or less to be able to use it, and barely anyone wants to take some crappy daring buff over hero or Natureskin.&quot;<br>
Education.  Lots of people think that if your yellow bar empties in combat you become less effective.  Lots of people thought that dex makes you hit more often.  Fallacies.  If you don't have a cleric in party for cheals, then max HP doesn't matter nearly as much.  If a 5-10% bonus in your max health is the difference between life and death wherever you are hunting, then you are taking on a place much too tough.  Use daring, and the daring helm, and be a better addition to your group than you would otherwise.<br>
<br>
To tell the truth, every time I see your lack of DW armor while your at the zone in Seb makes me think your equipment is less than appropriate.  I've partied with paladins that use DW armor, and the armor and spell effects add a lot to the group.  I've played a paladin with DW, and I KNOW how good the spell effects are.  If I had to pick you, with your total lack of DW armor, and a low 50s paladin with a few pieces of DW armor, I'd take the lower level one, because he actually knows what he's doing concerning his armor.<br>
<br>
Paladins are defensive tanks with backup heals and utility spells.  Paladins should have high AC, high resists, and use their spells to reduce damage and downtime taken by their group.  They control the aggro much better than warriors, allowing for other damage dealing classes to do their thing (keeping monks and rogues and casters from being attacked).  This is what good paladins do.   <p>=============================
<br>Juujuu Bigmojo
<br>60 Halfling Shaman
