Juujuu, you don't realize that even without c2 or even clarity, I have enough mana to maintain the chain stunning. I'm not shortsighted like you say I am, I have done my research, I know what I'm talking about. Quit downsizing my intelligence and debate this like a normal person would. You say one thing, I'm defending the other side. I say that the DW bracer is useless. If you are trying to maintain aggro, then it is stupid, just plain idiotic, to try to cast a spell that takes 6 seconds to cast. A mob can get in 3 swings on you, and most likely is going to hit you. <br>
<br>
I can easily get my ac over 1100, without clerical buffs. <br>
I've already debated the bracer, and have proven if you have the mana, DW is a worthless item to get, unless you don't care about stats and love the ac.<br>
<br>
And as far as a level 50 paladin knowing more about his armor than I have, I got to kind of smile. And if you want to choose a level 50 paladin because he uses DW armor over someone like me, who already has more ac than a paladin in DW anyway (thanks to Nature's Defender), well, your call. but you are going to have one lousy tank in high intense areas, and I gauruntee I'll perform better in ANY situation than a low 50's paladin with a few pieces of that precious deepwater armor.<br>
<br>
I've done my testing with the helmet. You want facts, then here we go.<br>
Superior healing takes 250mana (half a bub from me) and heals 600hp. The DW helm heals 120hp and takes no mana, but casts 6 seconds longer (the Daring taking 10sec to cast, Sup heal taking 4.5).<br>
Greater Healing only takes 150 mana but heals at only 300hp.<br>
<br>
Sup heal is mana efficient over Gheal. Now here is the kicker.<br>
<br>
With clarity2 on, I will med up the lost mana faster than it would take me to stand there and cast five darings (each daring 120hp.. 5 x 120 = 600, or one sup heal). That's 50 seconds to med. 50 seconds is a long time to be sitting, and I easily gain a half bub, EASILY, when I'm medding. Hell, even with normal clarity, I can get a little under a half bub in 50 seconds.<br>
<br>
Well, shaman, this paladin knows her @#%$, has done her testing, and have given the ball to you now.<br>
<br>
I've proven how ineffective DW is. The legs and gauntlets being the most useful perhaps, but everything else is second rate to Valorium. You lose valuable stats and resists when you de-equip your valorium in favor of DW. I've shown you my ac, and I have more ac than many warriors (it just so happens the ranger I was comparing myself to was some stupid uber ranger with ac out the ass). <br>
<br>
Maybe if you were to get some nice valorium pieces on your alt paladin, you would see the difference it makes.<br>
<br>
Almost none. Except higher stats. I only notice big melee changes when you hit the next centigrade ( 900, 1000, 1100, etc). With Valorium, I can keep well over 2000 mana, good stats (for a high elf anyway), and very good ac AND still maintain a good offensive edge.<br>
<br>
