<br>
Fenye, one change, perhaps a Golem Tear ring (AC 2 Str 2 Wis 6 Mana 10) from Chardok would make a good replacement for your Velium Wis ring?<br>
<br>
Also why do you prefer your neck item to an old world PMT?  Just curious.<br>
<br>
And for general knowledge, there are in my opinion two ways of playing a paladin: a way that ephasizes the Cleric nature and a way that emphasaizes the Warrior elements.  Both are effective, and both have their uses.  HE Paladins can, generally, emphasize the cleric nature of their class more effectively as they have more mojo to use their spells.  Conversely the Dwarven Paladin as a general rule of thumb can more effectively emphasize the Warrior element due to the natural stat bonus in Str and Sta.  Though these things can even out over time, typically players grow into thise rolls over time and have a difficult time adjusting post 50.<br>
<br>
If a player can adjust they have a highly adaptable Hybrid with many twists and skills that can be exploited.  It takes creativity and flair to really play a paladin well, as well as a great deal of experience.  Frankly if you have not played a paladin for a long period of time, it is dificult to appreciate the nuiances of the class.  <br>
<br>
One can subtely but effectively manage Hate with Stuns, Flame of Light and the DD line of Undead spells.  Though inferior, paladins are OFTEN asked to shoulder the buff burden to take presure of the cleric, and when no cleriuc is available the Ac and Symbol lines of buffs are indespensible.  <br>
<br>
Crowd control with non summoning mobs is Highly effective with root parking, as is pulling when Hich AC and Hp are needed to surve long run outs.  I can control a three mob pull without a mezzer by soloing/root parking 2 mobs easily, keeping them on me and myself alive while the rest of the group concentrates their fire on the primary target.  <br>
<br>
As a back up healer a paladin will save a group from a wipe out.  I have lost track of the times I have dumped all of my mana into heals and saved agroup when the healers are agrod/oom/dead/camped whatever.  I do not cound loh here, simply Gheal which is enough to barely stay ahed of a mobs damage output in many situations.<br>
<br>
And finaly, though rare as hell, paladins have one skill at the end of the game that is clearly highly desireable.  We can rez at 59.  Only a handful of palaidns ever gain this skill.  Most give up before they reach 59.  But what an amazing ability.<br>
