<br>
Now I looked at you equipment and it's all great equipment, but might not be best depending on what you you are going to have to play in the group.  Don't get me wrong it's great stuff and I'd love to walk around carrying that kinda items but heres why I think this way.  A Paladin can preform different tasks and in each group it could, and probally will be, different.  We can tank and heal, and crowd control to a certain extant.<br>
<br>
In a tank heavy group (this includes other pallys/sks/warriors) we need to be healers.  So drop the ac down a bit and get more wis, and a DW helm.  I say this because although we are a tank in this group let someone else take the hits, unless of course your all hybrids and you have more hp/ac then the others in this case let someone else be the main/back up healer.<br>
<br>
In a healer heavy group your expected to tank, drop that wis, you don't need it.  Throw on you ac gear and get hit.  If theres a lot of healers you shouldn't even need to mem your heal spells, although it's a good safty precaution.<br>
<br>
In a caster heavy group (This mean no healer or perhaps a druid/shammy healer), well this is the toughest kinda of group for us to fight in.  Not only are we expected to tank, but heal as well.  And in this type of group I would assume you shine in, cause with your stats I assume you can do both and still make out pretty well.  <br>
<br>
And last but not least the perfect group.  Now there will be a Warrior/Cleric/Chanter in this group.  And in all honesty we preform best in this group as well.  Now in this group, ac is nice but not king like most people think.  To a warrior is ac is always king, but here your spot on the hate list is far more important then anything.  Whenever there is a warrior in the group you arn't main tank and shouldn't be getting hit like you are.  Instead your job is to prevent damage to the warrior all while keeping under him on the hate list.  But controling the hate list is far harder then some think.  While a warrior can only hit the taunt button and use his fastest weapon, we have spells, so use them wisely, don't get above the warrior on the hate list.  Instead stay right under him so if you do feel the need to take a hit for him while the heal is comming all you need to do is hit the taunt button once.  And don't be afraind to turn you attack off, your not here to do large amounts of damage, you here to prevent the damage.  Stand back if needs be, but whatever you do chain stun him while the warrior/wiz/rogue/ranger/mage does damage.  <br>
<br>
Now onto the issue with DW and it's worth.  Now in some groups it's ac is second to none (Well it is to some of the Velious stuff, but really how many people get that) and in certain groups you'll need the ac.  And in some group you'll need the stats of the Valorium.  Now I'll agree with you, some of the DW effects are as lame as can be, but personally I would invest in atleast the DW bracer and helm.  I'm not saying wear them all the time, just be sure to have them if the group you in calls for you to have a role in which they would benefit you. <br>
<br>
3 more things to mention before I shut up.  One, you didn't say whats on your back, I would suggest trying for a Lod shield if you don't already have one.  And second, Why no Range item?  You could easily obtain An Idol of the Thorned (Ac10 Str7 Sta10), better then nothing.<br>
<br>
And lastly, are paladin useless?  No, we all may feel useless at times, but so does every other class out there.<br>
<br>
That's my 2 cents.<br>
