1) Paladins do not contribute enough damage to a fight to carry their own weight.<br>
<br>
2) Paladins cannot heal or provide enough utility to make up for their lack of offensive ability.<br>
<br>
I'd like to look at the problem a bit differently.  Consider a group of characters as a functional whole.  The group has HPs, mana, and melee damage capability.<br>
<br>
The group also has &quot;soft points&quot; where badly applied damage from mobs can cripple progress or wipe out the group altogether.<br>
<br>
Let's compare paladins to warriors.  According to what I've heard, a paladin is supposedly capable of achieving 2/3 of the melee damage of a warrior when hasted and wielding a good weapon.  Paladin AC and HPs are inferior to warriors as well, however they are by no means negligible.<br>
<br>
Paladins have mana, largely usable for stuns and backup heals.<br>
<br>
When protecting a soft point (i.e. non-tank), the 1.5 second stun seems to be a very ideal means to peel a mob off of a caster.  A heal thrown onto the caster could well save the him from death and simultaneously draw a mob onto the paladin for more effective tanking.  Warriors have Taunt and melee damage, but the advantage when keeping other groupmates alive is clearly the paladin's.<br>
<br>
Now let's compare the paladin to a cleric.  High level cleric heals and buffs are unmatchable by a paladin.  The paladin has melee damage that will certainly exceed what the cleric is capable of.<br>
<br>
When a cleric heals someone and picks up too much aggro, a paladin is still very handy.  Stun, heals, root are all good methods to use when peeling a critter off of someone.  The cleric gets to return to medition that much faster.<br>
<br>
Hopefully these two comparisons will show where paladins really shine.  I've grouped with many high level paladins who were all very good at keeping a mob's attention and surviving.  In light of this, I don't think badly of the class at all!<br>
<br>
Leewei <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.showMessageRange?topicID=504.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.showMessageRange?topicID=504.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.showMessageRange?topicID=504.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.showMessageRange?topicID=504.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a> <b>5</b> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.showMessageRange?topicID=504.topic&start=101&stop=117>6</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.showMessage?topicID=399.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.showMessage?topicID=543.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.threadControl?topicID=504.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=504.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=504.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="brellserilisfrm48">Town Crier (Rules & Announcements)<option value="brellserilisbrellseril